CHAPTER 3 – SYSTEM DESIGN
3.1 Overall Architecture
The system follows a multi-layered, scalable architecture that evolves step-by-step from data processing to a fully functional mobile-based prediction system. The design ensures clear separation between data handling, model processing, deployment, and user interaction, making the system modular, maintainable, and extensible.
The architecture is developed in a sequential manner. Initially, the work begins with dataset acquisition and preprocessing. Multiple datasets related to different mental health conditions are collected and stored in CSV format. These datasets include both structured and textual data, which require different processing techniques.
After dataset preparation, the next layer focuses on machine learning model development. Various algorithms are trained and evaluated, and the best-performing models are selected. These models are stored in PKL format as serialized objects.
In the next stage, the architecture transitions towards deployment. The trained PKL models are converted into ONNX format to ensure cross-platform compatibility and optimized inference performance. This step is critical because ONNX allows models to be used outside Python environments and supports integration with mobile and cloud systems.
Following model conversion, the ONNX models are deployed on Hugging Face. This creates an API layer that acts as a bridge between the backend models and the frontend application.
Finally, the Android application is developed, which serves as the user interface. The application sends requests to the API and receives predictions in real time.
Key Components of Architecture:
• Data Layer:
•	Stores raw datasets (CSV files)
•	Stores cleaned and processed datasets
•	Handles input data from users
• Processing Layer:
•	Data preprocessing and NLP operations
•	Feature extraction and transformation
•	Model training and evaluation
• Model Layer:
•	Contains trained ML models
•	Stores models in PKL format
•	Converts models to ONNX
• Deployment Layer:
•	Hosts ONNX models on Hugging Face
•	Provides API endpoints
• Application Layer:
•	Android application interface
•	Sends user input to API
•	Displays prediction results
• Communication Layer:
•	REST API communication
•	Handles request-response cycle
This layered architecture ensures flexibility, scalability, and ease of maintenance. It also allows independent updates to each component without affecting the entire system.
